### 1.4 Configuration System

#### [.env.example](file:///d:/IIT%20CODES/PROJECTS/AG%20auto-analytics-agent/.env.example)

Template file with all configurable environment variables:

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| `LLM_PROVIDER` | `openai` | Active LLM provider (`openai`, `gemini`, `ollama`) |
| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | вЂ” | OpenAI API key (user must fill) |
| `OPENAI_MODEL` | `gpt-4o` | OpenAI model name |
| `GOOGLE_API_KEY` | вЂ” | Google Gemini API key |
| `GEMINI_MODEL` | `gemini-1.5-pro` | Gemini model name |
| `OLLAMA_MODEL` | `llama3` | Local Ollama model |
| `APP_ENV` | `development` | Environment mode |
| `DEBUG` | `true` | Debug flag |
| `LOG_LEVEL` | `INFO` | Logging verbosity |
| `BACKEND_HOST` | `0.0.0.0` | FastAPI host |
| `BACKEND_PORT` | `8000` | FastAPI port |
| `FRONTEND_PORT` | `8501` | Streamlit port |
| `BACKEND_URL` | `http://localhost:8000` | URL frontend uses to reach backend |
| `CODE_EXECUTION_TIMEOUT` | `120` | Max seconds for sandboxed code |
| `MAX_RETRIES` | `3` | Self-healing retry limit |
| `MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE_MB` | `100` | Upload size cap |
| `MAX_ROWS_FOR_PROFILING` | `50000` | Row sampling limit |

#### [config/settings.py](file:///d:/IIT%20CODES/PROJECTS/AG%20auto-analytics-agent/config/settings.py)

Pydantic Settings class that:

- Automatically loads values from `.env` file
- Provides type-safe access to all config values
- Includes a `llm_model` computed property that returns the correct model name based on the active provider
- Exports a singleton `settings` instance for project-wide import:

```python
from config.settings import settings

print(settings.llm_provider)   # "openai"
print(settings.llm_model)      # "gpt-4o"
print(settings.debug)          # True
```

